xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104are1665702666827.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/are1665702666827.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/are1665702666827.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"are1665702666827\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"are1665702666827___columnsyntax_254640\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set or return the syntax attributes for the field displayed in a column of a grid or\n      multi-occurrence list.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"are1665702666827__topic_d80984e1_d80985e1_d80986e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d80987e1_d80988e1_d80989e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Field</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">) =</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeList</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d80990e1_d80991e1_d80992e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Result</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Field</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeList</var>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d80993e1_d80994e1_d80995e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"are1665702666827__topic_d53347e1_d53348e1_d53349e1_d53350e1_d53351e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017699e111\">Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__1\">Parameter</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__2\">Data Type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__3\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Field</var></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__2\">String </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__3\">\n Field name\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeList</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__2\">String </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8093e1_d8094e1_d8095e1__entry__3\">Uniface list of field syntax attributes, or an\n                        empty string. Although commas can be used when setting attributes, the\n                        retrieved list always uses GOLD ; as the separator. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Allowed Field Syntax Attributes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\">Code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Do not allow this field to be edited.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Do not prompt this field. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">HID</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Hide field. No display, no edit and no prompt.\n                        (Equivalent to <code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code> , and\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>.) <p class=\"p\">Not valid in character mode\n                              (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$GUI</code> =<code class=\"ph codeph\">$CHR</code> ).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DIM</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\"> Do not allow editing or prompt this field. In\n                        GUI mode, the field is dimmed; in character mode, it is equivalent to\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code>  and <code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">YDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Display this field.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">YED</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Allow this field to be edited. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">YPR</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8096e1_d8097e1_d8098e1__entry__2\">Prompt this field. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"are1665702666827__topic_d53352e1_d53353e1_d53354e1_d53355e1_d53356e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017699e307\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__d6494e20\">Use in Form and Report components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"are1665702666827__topic_d53357e1_d53358e1_d53359e1_d53360e1_d53361e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017699e316\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81008e1_d81009e1_d81010e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span> function to retrieve or set the syntax attributes of a collection of fields in the same column. For example, you can use this function to hide and show columns in a grid or multiple occurrence list.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81011e1_d81012e1_d81013e1\">The column syntax can only be reset by an explicit call with an empty string. The structure editor functions ^CLEAR and ^RETRIEVE have no influence on the column syntax.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"are1665702666827__topic_d53362e1_d53363e1_d53364e1_d53365e1_d53366e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1017699e332\">Combining <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span>\n</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81017e1_d81018e1_d81019e1\">The field syntax that is applied to a field is the result of the field syntax attributes that are set in the field definition, and using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span> (affecting the field in multiple occurrences) and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span> (affecting the field in a specific occurrence).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81020e1_d81021e1_d81022e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span> functions operate independently. Thus, if a field is set to No Prompt (<code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code>) with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span>, it cannot be reset using <code class=\"ph codeph\">$columnsyntax()=\"\"</code>. Similarly, If a field is hidden, it cannot be made visible by making the column visible.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81023e1_d81024e1_d81025e1\">For example:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"are1665702666827__li_d33761e1_d33762e1_d33763e1\">Hide the column for field FLD_B: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\"</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"are1665702666827__li_d33764e1_d33765e1_d33766e1\">Hide field FLD_B in the current occurrence: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$fieldsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\"</code>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81026e1_d81027e1_d81028e1\">Because the column has already been hidden, no change is visible.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"are1665702666827__li_d33767e1_d33768e1_d33769e1\">Show the column again:\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">$columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"\"</code>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"are1665702666827__p_d81029e1_d81030e1_d81031e1\">The column is displayed, but the FLD_B hidden by\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span> remains hidden.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Effect of Modeled Field Syntax Combined With <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$columnsyntax</span> and\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldsyntax</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__1\">Field Syntax</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__2\">$columnsyntax</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__3\">$fieldsyntax</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__4\">Result</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">YED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__4\">All fields in the column can be edited, get\n                        focus, and display the content.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">YED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__3\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__4\">\n All fields in the column can be edited, get focus, and display the characters, with the exception of the field in the current occurrence which is non-editable.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">NED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">NDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__3\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">YED</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YPR</code> ,<code class=\"ph codeph\">YDI</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"are1665702666827__table_d8099e1_d8100e1_d8101e1__entry__4\">\n All fields in the column are hidden and only one field is displayed in the default entity.\n <p class=\"p\">In the grid, the column is hidden but the field in the default entity can still be edited and get focus.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/roo1720021541651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>fieldsyntax (deprecated)</a><p>Set the syntax attributes of the specified field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525841\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$columnsyntax Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set or return the syntax attributes for the field displayed in a column of a grid or multi-occurrence list. $columnsyntax ( Field ) = AttributeList Result = $columnsyntax ( Field { , AttributeList } ) Example: $columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\" Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description Field String Field name AttributeList String Uniface list of field syntax attributes, or an empty string. Although commas can be used when setting attributes, the retrieved list always uses GOLD ; as the separator. Table 2. Allowed Field Syntax Attributes Code Description NED Do not allow this field to be edited. NPR Do not prompt this field. HID Hide field. No display, no edit and no prompt. (Equivalent to NDI , NED , and NPR .) Not valid in character mode ( $GUI = $CHR ). DIM Do not allow editing or prompt this field. In GUI mode, the field is dimmed; in character mode, it is equivalent to NED and NPR . YDI Display this field. YED Allow this field to be edited. YPR Prompt this field. Use Use in Form and Report components. Description Use the $columnsyntax function to retrieve or set the syntax attributes of a collection of fields in the same column. For example, you can use this function to hide and show columns in a grid or multiple occurrence list. The column syntax can only be reset by an explicit call with an empty string. The structure editor functions ^CLEAR and ^RETRIEVE have no influence on the column syntax. Combining $columnsyntax and $fieldsyntax The field syntax that is applied to a field is the result of the field syntax attributes that are set in the field definition, and using $columnsyntax (affecting the field in multiple occurrences) and $fieldsyntax (affecting the field in a specific occurrence). The $fieldsyntax and $columnsyntax functions operate independently. Thus, if a field is set to No Prompt ( NPR ) with $fieldsyntax , it cannot be reset using $columnsyntax()=\"\" . Similarly, If a field is hidden, it cannot be made visible by making the column visible. For example: Hide the column for field FLD_B: $columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\" Hide field FLD_B in the current occurrence: $fieldsyntax(FLD_B)=\"HID\" Because the column has already been hidden, no change is visible. Show the column again: $columnsyntax(FLD_B)=\"\" The column is displayed, but the FLD_B hidden by $fieldsyntax remains hidden. Table 3. Effect of Modeled Field Syntax Combined With $columnsyntax and $fieldsyntax Field Syntax $columnsyntax $fieldsyntax Result NED , NPR , NDI YED , YPR , YDI All fields in the column can be edited, get focus, and display the content. NED , NPR , NDI YED , YPR , YDI NED All fields in the column can be edited, get focus, and display the characters, with the exception of the field in the current occurrence which is non-editable. NED , NPR , NDI YED , YPR , YDI All fields in the column are hidden and only one field is displayed in the default entity. In the grid, the column is hidden but the field in the default entity can still be edited and get focus. Related Links fieldsyntax (deprecated) Set the syntax attributes of the specified field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}